The flagbearer of the Action Alliance (AA) in the November 6, 2021 governorship election in Anambra State, Chief Ben Etiaba, has congratulated Professor Charles Chukwuma Soludo on the occasion of his inauguration as governor of the state. Soludo, who was the candidate of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA), emerged the winner of the keenly-contested gubernatorial election, succeeded Chief Willie Obiano, whose two term of eight years as governor of the state elapsed on 17th March, 2022. Soludo, an ex-Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) was sworn in as 5th Governor of Anambra State Inna well attended ceremony on Thursday in, Awka, the Anambra State capital However, while reacting to the epoch- making inauguration ceremony in a statement forwarded to DAILY POST on Friday, Etiaba, expressed optimism that the new governor will take Anambra to greater height from where it is presently. According to the frontline politician, “whereas the unfortunate distraction at the event dominated the news headlines,let us all nonetheless lift a glass in honor of our new Governor who seems every bit determined to moving our state from where we presently are, to where we should be as the “Light of the Nation. “I join all well meaning men and women of goodwill in praying for him and his incoming team, for a successful tenure”, he added.